1
00:00:01,106 --> 00:00:03,442
[♪ pop music playing]

2
00:00:45,359 --> 00:00:49,071
PERFECT CROWN

3
00:00:59,956 --> 00:01:01,083
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:03,085
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:01:03,168 --> 00:01:04,753
PROMISING THE END, NOT FOREVER…

6
00:01:04,836 --> 00:01:06,755
EXCLUSIVE: THE ROYAL COUPLE'S
MARRIAGE CONTRACT LEAKED

7
00:01:06,838 --> 00:01:08,048
[reporters clamoring]

8
00:01:08,131 --> 00:01:10,300
[reporter 1] Is it true that
the marriage is contractual?

9
00:01:10,384 --> 00:01:13,428
[reporter 2] Is it true you plan to
divorce in three years? Please respond!

10
00:01:13,512 --> 00:01:15,764
ROYAL ACADEMY
80TH ANNIVERSARY CELEBRATION

11
00:01:15,847 --> 00:01:17,599
[reporter 3] Did you intentionally
deceive the people?

12
00:01:17,683 --> 00:01:19,559
[reporter 4]
This is a betrayal of the public!

13
00:01:20,894 --> 00:01:22,062
[chuckles]

14
00:01:24,731 --> 00:01:26,900
[reporter 5] What has Castle Group
promised the Crown?

15
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:45,001
[clamoring continues]

16
00:01:45,085 --> 00:01:47,879
-[reporter 6] Is it true?
-[reporter 7] Are the allegations true?

17
00:01:49,423 --> 00:01:50,549
[Huiju] What are you doing?

18
00:01:52,926 --> 00:01:53,927
Keep your eyes on me.

19
00:01:54,970 --> 00:01:56,471
[clamoring fades]

20
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:04,104
[clamoring resumes]

21
00:02:08,817 --> 00:02:10,068
[clamoring fades]

22
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:29,045
PERFECT CROWN

23
00:02:29,588 --> 00:02:31,131
EPISODE 9

24
00:02:37,804 --> 00:02:39,181
Let's get you out first.

25
00:02:39,681 --> 00:02:40,682
[Hyeon] Your Royal Highness.

26
00:02:41,558 --> 00:02:44,770
It's swarming with reporters
and students outside.

27
00:02:44,853 --> 00:02:46,480
What should we do?

28
00:02:46,563 --> 00:02:48,857
-And the Royal Guard?
-We had dispatched the bare minimum.

29
00:02:50,609 --> 00:02:51,610
[sighs]

30
00:02:55,947 --> 00:02:56,990
I'll leave first.

31
00:02:57,073 --> 00:02:58,700
-You two can--
-Your Royal Highness!

32
00:02:58,784 --> 00:02:59,951
I don't want to.

33
00:03:04,206 --> 00:03:05,248
Let's leave together.

34
00:03:05,332 --> 00:03:07,542
[♪ intriguing music playing]

35
00:03:21,932 --> 00:03:23,391
[reporters murmuring]

36
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,063
[reporter 1] There they are!

37
00:03:28,146 --> 00:03:29,940
[reporter 2] Any words
for the people watching?

38
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,733
[reporter 3] Is it all true?

39
00:03:34,819 --> 00:03:36,571
[reporter 4] Are the allegations true?

40
00:03:36,655 --> 00:03:38,240
[reporter 5] What comes after divorce?

41
00:03:38,323 --> 00:03:40,659
-Are you confirming the allegations?
-Your Royal Highness!

42
00:03:40,742 --> 00:03:41,993
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

43
00:03:42,994 --> 00:03:45,664
-Your Royal Highness, what say you?
-Are the allegations true?

44
00:03:45,747 --> 00:03:48,500
-Your Royal Highness!
-Please give us a response!

45
00:03:48,583 --> 00:03:49,918
[reporter 6] Are the allegations true?

46
00:03:50,001 --> 00:03:52,087
[reporter 7] Is it true that
this is a marriage of convenience?

47
00:03:52,170 --> 00:03:54,839
[both gasping, panting]

48
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:57,842
-Oh, no…
-They're tinted windows, Hyejeong.

49
00:03:57,926 --> 00:03:59,970
Really? Thank goodness.

50
00:04:00,053 --> 00:04:01,888
[panting]

51
00:04:08,186 --> 00:04:09,354
Right.

52
00:04:11,773 --> 00:04:12,774
[Hyeon clears throat]

53
00:04:14,818 --> 00:04:16,570
[grunts] Why isn't this working?
STYLE
::cue()

54
00:04:19,948 --> 00:04:21,575
They should be okay, right?

55
00:04:21,658 --> 00:04:24,327
I think so.
They have Prime Minister Min, so…

56
00:04:27,747 --> 00:04:31,167
Right. I should update
the Royal Guard. [chuckles]

57
00:04:31,251 --> 00:04:34,963
Right. I should also update
the Royal Secretariat.

58
00:04:35,046 --> 00:04:37,465
[reporter 1] Is there any truth
to the allegations?

59
00:04:39,134 --> 00:04:41,052
[reporter 2] Any response
to the allegations?

60
00:04:46,474 --> 00:04:47,559
[Lady Choi] We must hurry!

61
00:04:53,481 --> 00:04:54,691
Your Majesty.

62
00:04:56,610 --> 00:04:58,737
Where are the Grand Prince and Princess?

63
00:04:59,905 --> 00:05:01,573
You see, they are…

64
00:05:07,078 --> 00:05:08,163
[scoffs]

65
00:05:13,793 --> 00:05:15,879
Reporters are camped out
in front of the palace.

66
00:05:16,588 --> 00:05:18,089
This should be the safest option.

67
00:05:18,673 --> 00:05:19,674
[aide] Sir.

68
00:05:21,134 --> 00:05:22,844
The party is asking
about the crisis meeting.

69
00:05:22,928 --> 00:05:24,679
Tell them they'll have to wait.

70
00:05:24,763 --> 00:05:27,766
Make sure no one talks to the press
to avoid speculative coverage.

71
00:05:27,849 --> 00:05:29,184
Yes, sir.

72
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:31,686
Foreign Affairs is asking
about the overseas tour…

73
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,105
-[Jeongwoo] Submit it in writing.
-Yes, sir.

74
00:05:44,324 --> 00:05:47,118
[newscaster] Amid growing fallout
from the leaked marriage contract,

75
00:05:47,202 --> 00:05:50,956
the controversy is escalating
beyond a mere private-life scandal,

76
00:05:51,039 --> 00:05:54,250
even drawing scrutiny
over the monarchy's credibility.

77
00:05:54,334 --> 00:05:57,212
The alleged preferential treatment
the Grand Princess received,

78
00:05:57,295 --> 00:05:59,631
and the suspension
of the Junghwajeon fire investigation…

79
00:05:59,714 --> 00:06:02,133
[fading] …have emerged
as the central points of this controversy.

80
00:06:02,759 --> 00:06:03,885
[I-AN, distorted] Huiju.

81
00:06:05,512 --> 00:06:07,305
-Seong Huiju.
-[Huiju breathes heavily]

82
00:06:11,101 --> 00:06:13,019
-[normal] Seong Huiju.
-[newscaster] In response, the Crown

83
00:06:13,103 --> 00:06:16,564
has stated it is verifying the facts,
maintaining a cautious stance.

84
00:06:16,648 --> 00:06:19,526
However, critics argue
that the possibility of the exercise

85
00:06:19,609 --> 00:06:21,695
of private influence cannot be ruled out.

86
00:06:22,821 --> 00:06:25,156
Both the Crown and the Cabinet
are reportedly conducting…

87
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,574
Are you okay?

88
00:06:26,658 --> 00:06:29,119
[newscaster] However, neither has yet
released an official statement.

89
00:06:33,665 --> 00:06:34,666
Yes.

90
00:06:52,058 --> 00:06:53,268
[Jeongwoo sighs]

91
00:06:55,603 --> 00:06:57,397
Let's start by confirming a few things.

92
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,773
First of all,

93
00:06:58,857 --> 00:07:01,359
did you two draw up
the marriage contract yourselves?

94
00:07:08,366 --> 00:07:09,826
[exhales sharply]

95
00:07:09,909 --> 00:07:13,538
Besides me, does anyone else know
that this marriage is fake?

96
00:07:14,122 --> 00:07:15,749
Aside from my personal aide,

97
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:17,417
there's no one else.

98
00:07:19,544 --> 00:07:20,879
Just Ms. Do.

99
00:07:27,302 --> 00:07:29,345
I haven't discussed it
with the Royal Secretariat yet,

100
00:07:29,429 --> 00:07:32,599
but they will most likely
choose not to respond.

101
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:35,143
What do you mean?

102
00:07:35,226 --> 00:07:36,728
As long as the contract is real,

103
00:07:36,811 --> 00:07:38,938
any explanation or defense
will only stir up more noise.

104
00:07:39,022 --> 00:07:41,357
So, are you asking us to stay silent?

105
00:07:43,777 --> 00:07:45,904
Yes. Precisely, Your Royal Highness.

106
00:07:50,158 --> 00:07:52,911
Waiting for things
to die down could backfire on us.

107
00:07:52,994 --> 00:07:55,038
We must wait until even that dies down.

108
00:07:55,121 --> 00:07:56,498
It was only…

109
00:08:02,128 --> 00:08:03,421
a farce in the beginning.

110
00:08:04,130 --> 00:08:06,090
[♪ soft music playing]

111
00:08:13,723 --> 00:08:15,266
"It only started out as deception."

112
00:08:16,351 --> 00:08:17,435
Is that what you'll say?

113
00:08:19,646 --> 00:08:22,273
The contract stipulates
a divorce within three years.

114
00:08:22,357 --> 00:08:23,441
Can you guarantee

115
00:08:24,692 --> 00:08:25,819
there will be no divorce?

116
00:08:34,869 --> 00:08:36,120
Can you?
STYLE
::cue()

117
00:08:44,671 --> 00:08:46,005
[knocks on door]

118
00:08:46,089 --> 00:08:48,716
-[door opens]
-[footsteps approach]

119
00:08:50,051 --> 00:08:51,052
Sir.

120
00:08:52,345 --> 00:08:53,471
You really should see this.

121
00:08:58,184 --> 00:08:59,310
Excuse me for a moment.

122
00:09:04,691 --> 00:09:05,984
[sighs]

123
00:09:08,236 --> 00:09:09,237
[sighs]

124
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:12,365
I wondered why that brat
would just hand over the company.

125
00:09:12,448 --> 00:09:14,033
Turns out she had a whole plan.

126
00:09:14,117 --> 00:09:16,035
What about that kiss over the palace wall?

127
00:09:16,119 --> 00:09:17,162
Was that fake too?

128
00:09:17,245 --> 00:09:18,496
Of course, it was!

129
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:22,000
Then what about when she collapsed,
and he carried her out in his arms?

130
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:23,251
Was that all just an act?

131
00:09:23,334 --> 00:09:25,044
Babe, who cares about that right now?

132
00:09:25,128 --> 00:09:27,005
Our family is about to be ruined!

133
00:09:28,006 --> 00:09:30,175
Well, I'm just worried about Huiju…

134
00:09:30,258 --> 00:09:32,010
-[phone chiming]
-What is it now?

135
00:09:33,178 --> 00:09:34,470
What's with all the messages?

136
00:09:34,554 --> 00:09:36,598
ANOTHER SCANDAL WILL BREAK THIS WEEK…

137
00:09:36,681 --> 00:09:39,100
[journalist 1] I wondered why Prince I-AN
would marry a love child…

138
00:09:39,184 --> 00:09:41,186
[journalist 2] He clearly married
for Castle Group.

139
00:09:41,269 --> 00:09:42,896
[journalist 3] So all that talk
about Prince Suyang…

140
00:09:42,979 --> 00:09:44,939
[journalist 4] Was her fainting
at the wedding just a stunt?

141
00:09:45,023 --> 00:09:46,191
Babe.

142
00:09:46,816 --> 00:09:48,443
What the hell is going on?

143
00:09:50,653 --> 00:09:52,655
As public trust in the royal couple wavers

144
00:09:52,739 --> 00:09:56,618
following the leak
of their marriage contract earlier today,

145
00:09:56,701 --> 00:10:00,038
incendiary allegations have surfaced
that Grand Princess Seong received

146
00:10:00,121 --> 00:10:03,124
preferential treatment
even prior to the royal wedding.

147
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:06,502
Grand Princess Seong had previously
been identified as the prime suspect

148
00:10:06,586 --> 00:10:08,755
in the Junghwajeon Hall fire
that broke out

149
00:10:08,838 --> 00:10:10,882
during His Majesty's
Royal Birthday Banquet.

150
00:10:10,965 --> 00:10:14,594
Some critics argue that the Grand Prince
may have intervened in the investigation

151
00:10:14,677 --> 00:10:16,387
for personal reasons.

152
00:10:16,471 --> 00:10:18,932
Some are even voicing concerns

153
00:10:19,015 --> 00:10:22,602
whether he is connected
to the Junghwajeon Hall fire incident.

154
00:10:22,685 --> 00:10:26,356
The political sphere is adopting
a cautious stance,

155
00:10:26,439 --> 00:10:27,732
while the palace and the Cabinet…

156
00:10:36,407 --> 00:10:37,492
[I-AN] Are you scared?

157
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:42,914
You have to have honor
for disgrace to mean anything.

158
00:10:45,166 --> 00:10:46,960
I've never had any, so I'm fine.

159
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,300
[I-AN sighs]

160
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:56,719
Are you okay?

161
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:02,016
Honor is all you have.

162
00:11:09,565 --> 00:11:10,566
Are you scared?

163
00:11:13,695 --> 00:11:15,780
[♪ soft music playing]

164
00:11:24,372 --> 00:11:25,373
Yes.

165
00:11:29,627 --> 00:11:30,795
I am afraid…

166
00:11:34,257 --> 00:11:35,591
that my honor will end up…

167
00:11:38,594 --> 00:11:39,637
harming you.

168
00:11:42,265 --> 00:11:43,683
[door opens]

169
00:11:46,102 --> 00:11:47,103
I believe it's best

170
00:11:47,729 --> 00:11:49,647
for you both to return to the palace now.

171
00:11:49,731 --> 00:11:51,274
What about all the reporters there?

172
00:11:52,066 --> 00:11:53,359
Are you sure it's okay?

173
00:11:53,443 --> 00:11:57,238
[sighs] They're planning a protest
outside the palace tomorrow morning.

174
00:11:57,322 --> 00:11:58,448
A protest?

175
00:11:58,531 --> 00:11:59,907
What are you talking about?

176
00:12:01,826 --> 00:12:04,245
There's a rumor that
you're vying for the throne.

177
00:12:05,288 --> 00:12:08,082
The Junghwajeon fire is being interpreted
to fit that narrative.

178
00:12:08,166 --> 00:12:09,292
That's absolute nonsense.

179
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:12,045
[sighs] Securing your safety comes first.

180
00:12:12,587 --> 00:12:13,629
Return to the palace.

181
00:12:20,553 --> 00:12:24,349
It appears the protest cannot be stopped.

182
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:27,810
Nothing could possibly stop it now.

183
00:12:28,353 --> 00:12:31,647
To be loved is to be hated
in equal measure.

184
00:12:34,275 --> 00:12:37,403
Nothing stokes gossip like the downfall
of the high and mighty.

185
00:12:39,781 --> 00:12:41,324
Did you deliver the message to Father?

186
00:12:41,407 --> 00:12:43,326
He sent word that he is on his way.

187
00:12:47,205 --> 00:12:49,207
[♪ ominous music playing]

188
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,877
Prepare to enter the Council Hall.
STYLE
::cue()

189
00:13:06,307 --> 00:13:07,392
Your Royal Highness.

190
00:13:07,475 --> 00:13:09,394
You should make your way
to the Council Hall.

191
00:13:09,477 --> 00:13:10,478
Now?

192
00:13:10,561 --> 00:13:13,189
Her Majesty has summoned
the Office of Royal Relatives.

193
00:13:23,825 --> 00:13:26,035
[royal relatives chattering]

194
00:13:40,758 --> 00:13:42,760
[herald] Announcing Grand Prince I-AN.

195
00:13:46,305 --> 00:13:48,307
[royal relatives grunting]

196
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:54,063
Your Majesty.

197
00:13:56,107 --> 00:13:58,359
Have you summoned the royal relatives?

198
00:14:01,279 --> 00:14:04,490
-Let's discuss it privately.
-I do not wish to hear your excuses.

199
00:14:04,574 --> 00:14:06,284
-Queen Mother.
-How dare you!

200
00:14:07,827 --> 00:14:09,370
To deceive the people

201
00:14:10,413 --> 00:14:12,165
and bring disgrace upon the Crown.

202
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:16,252
[♪ tense music playing]

203
00:14:18,629 --> 00:14:20,548
Do you truly believe you can be forgiven?

204
00:14:29,974 --> 00:14:32,268
You, who sold off your royal status.

205
00:14:33,311 --> 00:14:35,229
And you, who purchased it.

206
00:14:36,606 --> 00:14:38,733
You would do well to prepare yourselves.

207
00:14:42,403 --> 00:14:44,322
I found it rather peculiar from the start,

208
00:14:44,405 --> 00:14:47,158
how she seemed to have no regard
for royal tradition or decorum.

209
00:14:47,241 --> 00:14:48,451
You should stop there.

210
00:14:48,534 --> 00:14:50,244
"It is simply
because of her low pedigree."

211
00:14:52,079 --> 00:14:53,706
That was my oversight.

212
00:15:02,924 --> 00:15:06,761
You thought you could protect yourself
with that measly contract?

213
00:15:06,844 --> 00:15:09,263
I cannot tell if you are naïve or foolish.

214
00:15:10,765 --> 00:15:11,974
[breathes shakily]

215
00:15:19,398 --> 00:15:20,983
Senior Sixth Rank, Choi Hyeon.

216
00:15:21,734 --> 00:15:22,818
Yes, Your Majesty.

217
00:15:22,902 --> 00:15:24,403
Junior Sixth Rank, Do Hyejeong.

218
00:15:24,487 --> 00:15:25,905
Yes, Your Majesty.

219
00:15:25,988 --> 00:15:28,783
Your superiors are unworthy
of an audience in the Council Hall.

220
00:15:30,451 --> 00:15:31,452
Escort them out.

221
00:15:43,089 --> 00:15:44,090
[Huiju] Your Royal Highness.

222
00:15:48,719 --> 00:15:49,720
Your Royal Highness!

223
00:15:57,228 --> 00:15:58,229
Your Royal Highness.

224
00:15:59,605 --> 00:16:01,023
[sighs] Your Royal Highness.

225
00:16:01,607 --> 00:16:03,734
[breathes shakily] I'm fine, so just…

226
00:16:03,818 --> 00:16:05,194
You're far from fine!

227
00:16:09,699 --> 00:16:10,783
[exclaims]

228
00:16:11,284 --> 00:16:13,160
Who clenches their fist this hard
out of anger?

229
00:16:14,954 --> 00:16:16,539
Just look at this hand.

230
00:16:17,707 --> 00:16:18,833
Stay put.

231
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:20,960
I'll have Aide Choi get some…

232
00:16:22,253 --> 00:16:24,505
[♪ soft music playing]

233
00:16:25,548 --> 00:16:26,924
[I-AN sighs]

234
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:28,801
I'm fine.

235
00:16:30,928 --> 00:16:31,929
It doesn't hurt.

236
00:16:36,726 --> 00:16:37,893
[I-AN sighs]

237
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:01,542
[Hyejeong gasps]

238
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:02,626
This is insane.

239
00:17:02,710 --> 00:17:04,295
It's hit the lower limit.

240
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:07,798
What if the chairman calls me
to his office? That won't end well.

241
00:17:07,882 --> 00:17:08,883
Hello.

242
00:17:10,426 --> 00:17:11,510
Seriously?

243
00:17:12,219 --> 00:17:13,262
[Hyeon] Aide Do!

244
00:17:13,846 --> 00:17:14,847
Yes?

245
00:17:15,598 --> 00:17:16,974
We have a problem.

246
00:17:17,058 --> 00:17:18,309
Why? What is it now?

247
00:17:18,392 --> 00:17:21,687
There's an article claiming
the Grand Princess faked her collapse.

248
00:17:22,688 --> 00:17:23,814
What?

249
00:17:23,898 --> 00:17:25,191
What are you talking about?

250
00:17:26,484 --> 00:17:27,485
THE REASON WHY SHE FAINTED…

251
00:17:27,568 --> 00:17:28,569
WAS THE COLLAPSE STAGED?

252
00:17:28,652 --> 00:17:29,654
Huh?
STYLE
::cue()

253
00:17:30,571 --> 00:17:31,572
It sounds like…

254
00:17:32,156 --> 00:17:33,824
This is about to blow up in our face.

255
00:17:33,908 --> 00:17:36,035
WAS THE COLLAPSE STAGED?
PRESSURE MOUNTS ON ROYAL FAMILY

256
00:17:36,118 --> 00:17:39,538
[protester] Remove Grand Prince I-AN
as regent!

257
00:17:39,622 --> 00:17:41,207
[protesters chanting]
Remove him! Remove him!

258
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:43,834
[protester] Grand Prince I-AN
and Seong Huiju must apologize!

259
00:17:43,918 --> 00:17:45,753
[protesters chanting]
Apologize! Apologize!

260
00:17:45,836 --> 00:17:49,423
[protester] Remove Grand Prince I-AN
as regent!

261
00:17:49,507 --> 00:17:51,133
[protesters chanting]
Remove him! Remove him!

262
00:17:51,217 --> 00:17:54,512
[protester] Strip Seong Huiju
of her rank immediately!

263
00:17:54,595 --> 00:17:55,680
[protesters chanting]
Immediately! Immediately!

264
00:17:55,763 --> 00:17:57,765
[♪ soft music playing]

265
00:18:05,773 --> 00:18:07,191
We cannot wait any longer.

266
00:18:08,693 --> 00:18:09,694
Your Royal Highness.

267
00:18:10,277 --> 00:18:11,821
They're going so far as to suggest

268
00:18:13,072 --> 00:18:14,907
that my wife fainted for show.

269
00:18:17,660 --> 00:18:19,453
I shall set the record straight myself.

270
00:18:22,832 --> 00:18:25,960
Our marriage may have started
with a contract,

271
00:18:27,253 --> 00:18:30,506
but everything we've shown the people
is genuine.

272
00:18:30,589 --> 00:18:31,674
Your Royal Highness.

273
00:18:31,757 --> 00:18:33,259
Even if the substance found in her system

274
00:18:34,802 --> 00:18:35,928
was one prescribed to me,

275
00:18:37,263 --> 00:18:40,599
there is nothing I seek to gain
at the cost of her life.

276
00:18:43,102 --> 00:18:45,604
What about the claim
that you're vying for the crown?

277
00:18:47,815 --> 00:18:49,442
Will you deny that as well?

278
00:18:51,736 --> 00:18:53,612
-Prime Minister Min.
-Answer me, sir.

279
00:18:54,405 --> 00:18:55,656
Will you deny it?

280
00:19:01,036 --> 00:19:02,329
If I do not deny it,

281
00:19:05,541 --> 00:19:07,251
how would you respond?

282
00:19:15,593 --> 00:19:18,429
"We do not need a king
who lacks the people's support."

283
00:19:19,138 --> 00:19:20,431
That's how I would respond.

284
00:19:25,811 --> 00:19:26,979
Thus, Your Royal Highness…

285
00:19:29,690 --> 00:19:31,609
For the sake of the Crown and the nation,

286
00:19:33,861 --> 00:19:34,862
I humbly request…

287
00:19:37,114 --> 00:19:38,324
that you end your regency.

288
00:19:52,338 --> 00:19:54,340
5 DAYS BEFORE THE CONTRACT LEAK

289
00:19:54,423 --> 00:19:55,424
Sir.

290
00:20:04,433 --> 00:20:07,520
They discovered traces of digoxin
in a goblet used in the wedding rites.

291
00:20:07,603 --> 00:20:09,355
PHOTO 1: GOBLET CONTAINING
TRACES OF DIGOXIN

292
00:20:09,438 --> 00:20:10,940
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

293
00:20:11,607 --> 00:20:13,484
Sir, Ms. Lee Areum has arrived.

294
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,661
[stammering] I heard you asked to see me.

295
00:20:28,541 --> 00:20:30,042
PERSONAL DETAILS: LEE AREUM

296
00:20:30,125 --> 00:20:31,210
IN CHARGE OF THE NUPTIAL WINE

297
00:20:31,293 --> 00:20:33,379
PARK MALJA, HER MOTHER,
BECAME AN ALCOHOLIC…

298
00:20:33,462 --> 00:20:35,631
IN NEED OF FUNDS
FOR BROTHER'S KIDNEY TRANSPLANT

299
00:20:42,930 --> 00:20:44,473
[Areum on speakers]
I was instructed to simply grind it up

300
00:20:44,557 --> 00:20:47,685
and rub it on the Grand Prince's goblet.

301
00:20:47,768 --> 00:20:50,312
I had no idea what it was.

302
00:20:50,396 --> 00:20:52,022
I was told if I didn't do it,

303
00:20:52,106 --> 00:20:54,108
my brother's surgery might be delayed…

304
00:20:56,527 --> 00:20:58,195
[sighs]

305
00:20:59,154 --> 00:21:00,322
Do you think it's true?

306
00:21:01,407 --> 00:21:02,575
We'll have to verify it.

307
00:21:06,078 --> 00:21:07,496
[sighs]

308
00:21:11,083 --> 00:21:12,585
But I still don't understand why.

309
00:21:16,922 --> 00:21:18,424
Did they really need to kill him?

310
00:21:20,634 --> 00:21:21,886
I get that he was bothersome…

311
00:21:29,852 --> 00:21:32,396
4 DAYS BEFORE THE CONTRACT LEAK

312
00:21:33,022 --> 00:21:34,023
Prime Minister Min.

313
00:21:35,107 --> 00:21:37,276
What could you possibly
be suggesting right now?

314
00:21:43,699 --> 00:21:45,492
Here's evidence
proving it was a poisoning.

315
00:21:49,538 --> 00:21:52,625
A staff testified that the Grand Prince
was the intended target.

316
00:21:52,708 --> 00:21:55,544
She confirmed the substance used
and her cryptocurrency records.

317
00:21:56,462 --> 00:21:57,630
She also testified

318
00:21:59,089 --> 00:22:01,258
that the compensation
came from Lord INPYEONG.

319
00:22:02,968 --> 00:22:04,011
This is slander.

320
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:09,350
How dare you suspect my father
on a mere servant's word?
STYLE
::cue()

321
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:11,685
-You are also under suspicion.
-Prime Minister Min!

322
00:22:11,769 --> 00:22:13,395
Can you prove you had no knowledge

323
00:22:14,897 --> 00:22:16,357
of Lord INPYEONG's actions?

324
00:22:25,741 --> 00:22:26,951
[servant] Your Majesty,

325
00:22:27,034 --> 00:22:28,827
Grand Prince I-AN has arrived.

326
00:22:43,050 --> 00:22:44,593
His Royal Highness remains unaware.

327
00:22:48,931 --> 00:22:50,099
Allow me some time.

328
00:22:59,024 --> 00:23:00,109
[servant] Your Majesty.

329
00:23:00,943 --> 00:23:02,194
Prime Minister Min.

330
00:23:04,613 --> 00:23:05,614
Until tonight.

331
00:23:07,950 --> 00:23:09,243
That is all I can provide you.

332
00:23:14,415 --> 00:23:15,749
I shall send word.

333
00:23:30,139 --> 00:23:31,932
What brings you here, Prime Minister Min?

334
00:23:32,016 --> 00:23:34,351
I came to request her cooperation
in the investigation.

335
00:23:34,435 --> 00:23:35,978
The Inner Court will be summoned tomorrow.

336
00:24:03,464 --> 00:24:05,424
I'm here to discuss
the Anhwadang Hall staff.

337
00:24:14,391 --> 00:24:15,392
Your Majesty?

338
00:24:18,979 --> 00:24:19,980
[grunts]

339
00:24:21,231 --> 00:24:24,109
I heard you were looking
to replace the attendants.

340
00:24:25,736 --> 00:24:28,530
Are you feeling unwell?

341
00:24:30,741 --> 00:24:32,659
The Grand Princess collapsed
at the wedding.

342
00:24:33,702 --> 00:24:36,246
Now, the Grand Prince seeks
to replace innocent attendants.

343
00:24:37,539 --> 00:24:39,166
The palace is in disarray, is it not?

344
00:24:43,796 --> 00:24:44,797
[sighs]

345
00:24:55,057 --> 00:24:56,058
[Huiju] Jeongwoo!

346
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:00,395
Should you be outside already?

347
00:25:00,479 --> 00:25:01,647
Did the doctor…

348
00:25:01,730 --> 00:25:03,982
[groans] I don't need to hear that
from you too.

349
00:25:04,066 --> 00:25:06,151
My ears are about to bleed as it is.

350
00:25:06,235 --> 00:25:09,905
It appears she is weary from all the care
the Grand Prince has taken

351
00:25:09,988 --> 00:25:11,573
to protect the Grand Princess.

352
00:25:11,657 --> 00:25:14,993
Given how devoted they are to each other,
producing an heir should not be…

353
00:25:15,077 --> 00:25:16,829
What… [laughs]

354
00:25:16,912 --> 00:25:19,331
…in the world are you talking about?

355
00:25:19,414 --> 00:25:21,583
In broad daylight, no less.

356
00:25:21,667 --> 00:25:22,751
[chuckles]

357
00:25:25,129 --> 00:25:26,713
Are you free for a short walk?

358
00:25:28,799 --> 00:25:29,883
Hmm.

359
00:25:30,759 --> 00:25:32,261
How's the investigation going?

360
00:25:32,886 --> 00:25:34,054
Are you getting anywhere?

361
00:25:35,347 --> 00:25:38,809
Can we trust Royal Seoul Hospital?

362
00:25:39,601 --> 00:25:41,228
If you want, I can have Castle Hospital…

363
00:25:44,189 --> 00:25:45,190
What?

364
00:25:47,484 --> 00:25:48,610
It seems real.

365
00:25:49,236 --> 00:25:50,237
What does?

366
00:25:51,113 --> 00:25:52,114
Your devotion?

367
00:25:52,197 --> 00:25:54,950
[sighs] Devotion? As if.

368
00:25:55,033 --> 00:25:58,162
Can't I even show
this much concern for my spouse?

369
00:26:02,958 --> 00:26:04,334
My goodness.

370
00:26:08,338 --> 00:26:10,716
You know our marriage is only for show.

371
00:26:12,092 --> 00:26:14,011
How are we supposed to fool the nation

372
00:26:14,094 --> 00:26:15,762
if we can't even fool the staff?

373
00:26:17,806 --> 00:26:18,807
So?

374
00:26:19,975 --> 00:26:21,268
You're trying to fool me too?

375
00:26:21,894 --> 00:26:22,936
What?

376
00:26:25,898 --> 00:26:26,940
[Mr. Jung] Sir.

377
00:26:32,613 --> 00:26:35,073
His Majesty is due to give
his witness statement shortly.

378
00:26:38,869 --> 00:26:39,912
I should go.

379
00:26:41,955 --> 00:26:43,373
But I'm not done talking yet…

380
00:26:44,416 --> 00:26:46,084
I'll call you later… [stammers]
STYLE
::cue()

381
00:26:57,804 --> 00:26:59,806
[Jeongwoo] Evidence that proves
it was a poisoning.

382
00:27:00,599 --> 00:27:03,685
A staff testified that the Grand Prince
was the intended target.

383
00:27:03,769 --> 00:27:06,730
She confirmed the drug used
and her cryptocurrency records.

384
00:27:09,316 --> 00:27:11,568
She testified the compensation
came from Lord INPYEONG.

385
00:27:16,406 --> 00:27:17,407
[door opens]

386
00:27:20,577 --> 00:27:21,578
Your Majesty.

387
00:27:22,204 --> 00:27:23,789
What brings you here unannounced?

388
00:27:25,499 --> 00:27:26,625
Explain yourself.

389
00:27:27,417 --> 00:27:28,669
-Your Majesty.
-I said!

390
00:27:31,672 --> 00:27:32,923
Explain yourself.

391
00:27:52,150 --> 00:27:53,443
Tell me it was not you.

392
00:27:53,986 --> 00:27:55,195
PERSONAL DETAILS: LEE AREUM

393
00:27:55,278 --> 00:27:56,989
WITNESS STATEMENT

394
00:27:59,741 --> 00:28:01,284
Where did you get this?

395
00:28:06,873 --> 00:28:09,376
I asked where you got this.

396
00:28:11,294 --> 00:28:13,588
Were you truly attempting to murder
the Grand Prince?

397
00:28:13,672 --> 00:28:15,674
[♪ dramatic music playing]

398
00:28:17,259 --> 00:28:18,593
Have you lost your mind?

399
00:28:19,261 --> 00:28:22,389
If this gets out,
you, me, and His Majesty will be--

400
00:28:22,472 --> 00:28:23,473
That is…

401
00:28:26,184 --> 00:28:29,354
exactly why the Grand Prince
must be eliminated.

402
00:28:34,109 --> 00:28:37,779
Why do you think the Grand Prince,
who feigned ignorance,

403
00:28:37,863 --> 00:28:40,240
has chosen to speak up now?

404
00:28:40,949 --> 00:28:43,827
Not only did you burn
the late King's final royal edict.

405
00:28:43,910 --> 00:28:45,412
But imagine

406
00:28:46,163 --> 00:28:48,915
what would happen if he discovers
the same fire killed the late King.

407
00:28:48,999 --> 00:28:50,917
I had nothing to do
with the late King's death!

408
00:28:51,001 --> 00:28:52,586
Who would ever believe

409
00:28:53,128 --> 00:28:55,464
such a feeble excuse?

410
00:28:58,091 --> 00:28:59,843
[breathes shakily] Father…

411
00:28:59,926 --> 00:29:01,887
"I only intended to burn the royal edict.

412
00:29:01,970 --> 00:29:03,555
I never intended for that fire

413
00:29:04,264 --> 00:29:07,100
to burn down the palace hall
and take the King's life."

414
00:29:08,769 --> 00:29:10,228
Is that what you will say?

415
00:29:17,736 --> 00:29:19,988
Is that what you have thought of me
all this time?

416
00:29:30,457 --> 00:29:34,669
What Your Majesty has done
is not my concern.

417
00:29:36,004 --> 00:29:38,507
You must do whatever it takes
to keep His Majesty safe.

418
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:40,759
That is the only way

419
00:29:40,842 --> 00:29:43,011
to ensure your own safety,

420
00:29:43,095 --> 00:29:45,263
mine, and our family name.

421
00:30:01,113 --> 00:30:02,572
Now, tell me.

422
00:30:04,741 --> 00:30:05,909
Where did you

423
00:30:07,494 --> 00:30:09,538
get this from?

424
00:30:35,814 --> 00:30:37,149
Your Majesty.

425
00:30:41,903 --> 00:30:42,904
Grand Princess.

426
00:30:49,411 --> 00:30:51,121
You would do well to tread carefully.

427
00:31:06,928 --> 00:31:07,929
[intercom beeps]

428
00:31:08,972 --> 00:31:09,973
[assistant] Sir.

429
00:31:10,056 --> 00:31:11,683
The Queen Mother is calling. It's urgent.

430
00:31:12,184 --> 00:31:15,061
-I'll connect you now.
-[phone buzzing, ringing]

431
00:31:18,523 --> 00:31:20,150
HUIJU

432
00:31:27,782 --> 00:31:30,076
[ringing continues]
STYLE
::cue()

433
00:31:36,124 --> 00:31:42,047
3 DAYS BEFORE THE CONTRACT LEAK

434
00:32:22,170 --> 00:32:23,505
How does it feel

435
00:32:24,005 --> 00:32:27,259
to have the man hailed
as the greatest prime minister in history

436
00:32:28,218 --> 00:32:29,469
as a father?

437
00:32:29,552 --> 00:32:30,762
PRIME MINISTER MIN SEUNGJAE

438
00:32:33,473 --> 00:32:34,474
I'm not sure.

439
00:32:35,642 --> 00:32:38,687
How does it feel
to have a father who will be known

440
00:32:38,770 --> 00:32:39,980
as the most dangerous lord

441
00:32:41,106 --> 00:32:42,482
in history?

442
00:32:44,859 --> 00:32:46,820
That will not be his legacy.

443
00:32:48,697 --> 00:32:49,781
Are you denying it?

444
00:32:51,616 --> 00:32:53,326
I wish to make a request.

445
00:32:54,786 --> 00:32:58,206
I thought about what would lead you
to bring me that evidence.

446
00:33:00,292 --> 00:33:02,544
If I were a suspect in your eyes…

447
00:33:05,463 --> 00:33:07,966
why did you come to me
and not the Grand Prince?

448
00:33:11,344 --> 00:33:13,221
Do you wish to have the Grand Princess?

449
00:33:20,562 --> 00:33:21,604
[sighs]

450
00:33:38,788 --> 00:33:40,248
MARRIAGE CONTRACT

451
00:33:40,332 --> 00:33:41,624
Should that come to light,

452
00:33:41,708 --> 00:33:43,918
the court will be in turmoil
and the nation in chaos.

453
00:33:46,254 --> 00:33:48,840
All the benefits outlined in the contract
favor the Grand Princess.

454
00:33:48,923 --> 00:33:51,718
Thus, the tide of condemnation
will break upon her.

455
00:33:55,096 --> 00:33:57,432
Do you think I would just let that happen?

456
00:33:58,058 --> 00:34:00,143
It is clear you are intent
on taking her for yourself.

457
00:34:02,145 --> 00:34:04,272
And you do not want her to suffer, either?

458
00:34:07,525 --> 00:34:08,860
Then,

459
00:34:10,278 --> 00:34:13,448
I shall redirect that tide to Prince I-AN.

460
00:34:15,158 --> 00:34:18,161
The more the Grand Prince
is driven to the brink,

461
00:34:19,162 --> 00:34:22,040
the more her resolve
is bound to crumble, is it not?

462
00:34:25,085 --> 00:34:26,211
[chuckles]

463
00:34:26,711 --> 00:34:27,837
What is the matter?

464
00:34:28,546 --> 00:34:31,007
Did you presume I could not perceive

465
00:34:31,925 --> 00:34:34,135
what you so plainly see between them?

466
00:34:37,138 --> 00:34:39,099
[Huiju] The Grand Prince smiles
when he drives too.

467
00:34:39,182 --> 00:34:41,309
He can be so childlike sometimes.

468
00:34:41,393 --> 00:34:43,311
He's in danger right now!

469
00:34:44,145 --> 00:34:45,397
I like Seong Huiju.

470
00:34:47,649 --> 00:34:49,567
You have tonight to consider your options.

471
00:34:50,944 --> 00:34:52,487
That is all I can provide you.

472
00:35:21,766 --> 00:35:23,560
[♪ somber music playing]
STYLE
::cue()

473
00:36:38,927 --> 00:36:41,012
Do you possess the authority to request…

474
00:36:43,973 --> 00:36:45,266
that I end the regency?

475
00:36:47,519 --> 00:36:49,312
I have a duty to protect the Crown.

476
00:36:50,104 --> 00:36:51,105
[scoffs]

477
00:36:53,274 --> 00:36:54,442
You make it sound…

478
00:36:56,903 --> 00:36:59,030
as though I sought to harm it.

479
00:37:00,031 --> 00:37:01,783
The Crown represents the nation.

480
00:37:03,368 --> 00:37:05,662
As long as you represent the Crown,

481
00:37:05,745 --> 00:37:07,038
you and the Crown

482
00:37:07,789 --> 00:37:09,082
are one.

483
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:11,835
So?

484
00:37:13,586 --> 00:37:14,712
Face your downfall alone.

485
00:37:17,549 --> 00:37:18,800
I will not allow you

486
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:22,470
to drag the Crown down with you.

487
00:37:34,816 --> 00:37:35,817
[scoffs]

488
00:37:44,492 --> 00:37:46,286
A private meeting with Prime Minister Min?

489
00:37:46,369 --> 00:37:49,205
Yes, Your Majesty.
They started early this morning.

490
00:37:49,289 --> 00:37:51,249
It has already been three hours.

491
00:37:51,791 --> 00:37:53,710
The Cabinet must be feeling
the pressure as well.

492
00:37:57,714 --> 00:37:58,715
What about Seong Huiju?

493
00:37:59,632 --> 00:38:00,758
Pardon?

494
00:38:00,842 --> 00:38:03,720
Is the Grand Princess alone right now?

495
00:38:04,470 --> 00:38:05,513
[Huiju] What?

496
00:38:06,806 --> 00:38:09,392
He told him to end his regency?
Jeongwoo did?

497
00:38:09,475 --> 00:38:10,476
[Hyeon] Yes.

498
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:13,605
I mean, I really trusted
Prime Minister Min.

499
00:38:13,688 --> 00:38:15,023
I know we're in a tight spot and all,

500
00:38:15,106 --> 00:38:17,567
but it's not like he doesn't know
what's going on.

501
00:38:17,650 --> 00:38:19,235
They crossed a line here, didn't they?

502
00:38:21,863 --> 00:38:23,781
The Queen Mother is asking for you.

503
00:38:23,865 --> 00:38:25,283
Well, I'm about to lose it. [scoffs]

504
00:38:44,719 --> 00:38:46,179
How does it feel?

505
00:38:49,307 --> 00:38:51,768
How does it feel to have dragged down

506
00:38:53,227 --> 00:38:55,688
the cherished prince of the nation?

507
00:39:00,860 --> 00:39:02,654
He had his moments of eccentricity

508
00:39:02,737 --> 00:39:04,906
and would sometimes go astray,

509
00:39:06,658 --> 00:39:09,285
but until he met you, I-AN was…

510
00:39:11,621 --> 00:39:13,373
the pride of the Crown.

511
00:39:18,336 --> 00:39:20,588
What did you offer him?

512
00:39:23,424 --> 00:39:25,259
What did he gain

513
00:39:26,469 --> 00:39:28,429
by elevating you so?

514
00:39:35,228 --> 00:39:36,229
[chuckles]

515
00:39:37,438 --> 00:39:38,898
Did you not read the contract?

516
00:39:41,067 --> 00:39:43,903
His Royal Highness
does not want anything from me.

517
00:39:46,155 --> 00:39:48,866
He even settled for three years,
as long as I was with him.

518
00:39:51,494 --> 00:39:53,037
So I simply agreed to do so.

519
00:39:58,126 --> 00:39:59,711
[♪ pensive music playing]

520
00:40:21,941 --> 00:40:24,569
[Yun] How does it feel
to have dragged down

521
00:40:24,652 --> 00:40:27,113
the cherished prince of the nation?

522
00:40:35,079 --> 00:40:36,080
Your Royal Highness.

523
00:40:37,290 --> 00:40:38,958
You should head to the King's Quarters.

524
00:40:39,042 --> 00:40:40,626
Has His Majesty summoned me?

525
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:42,628
I believe Lord INPYEONG is there

526
00:40:42,712 --> 00:40:44,422
with a formal appeal to the king

527
00:40:44,505 --> 00:40:45,631
and even a public petition.

528
00:40:51,679 --> 00:40:52,930
[Hyejeong] Emergency.

529
00:40:53,014 --> 00:40:54,474
Come to the King's Quarters
when you see this.

530
00:40:59,979 --> 00:41:02,065
THE NOBLE COUNCIL LEADER
AND 190 MEMBERS…

531
00:41:02,148 --> 00:41:03,441
THE LOVE STORY
THAT FOOLED THE NATION…

532
00:41:03,524 --> 00:41:04,525
[Lord INPYEONG] Your Majesty.

533
00:41:05,193 --> 00:41:07,195
The Crown will crumble at this rate.

534
00:41:07,278 --> 00:41:09,322
Even the Grand Prince

535
00:41:09,405 --> 00:41:11,783
cannot defy your royal command.

536
00:41:12,825 --> 00:41:14,368
But Uncle…

537
00:41:14,452 --> 00:41:15,745
Your Majesty!
STYLE
::cue()

538
00:41:17,580 --> 00:41:20,041
Have you not heard the rumors
spreading among the people?

539
00:41:20,833 --> 00:41:23,711
-The fire that took the late king…
-That is not true!

540
00:41:24,462 --> 00:41:26,047
Father was not…

541
00:41:26,130 --> 00:41:27,882
The Grand Prince knows that you are weak,
that is why--

542
00:41:27,965 --> 00:41:29,383
[Jung] Your Majesty.

543
00:41:29,467 --> 00:41:31,052
The Grand Prince…

544
00:41:33,262 --> 00:41:34,263
[sighs]

545
00:41:41,771 --> 00:41:44,690
How dare you show
such insolence before His Majesty!

546
00:41:44,774 --> 00:41:46,150
How dare you!

547
00:41:49,779 --> 00:41:51,572
How dare you threaten His Majesty?

548
00:41:54,909 --> 00:41:56,202
Why you…

549
00:41:57,078 --> 00:41:58,746
Uncle…

550
00:41:59,664 --> 00:42:00,915
Enter, Court Lady Jung.

551
00:42:03,126 --> 00:42:05,002
[gasps] Your Royal Highness!

552
00:42:05,878 --> 00:42:06,963
Escort His Majesty out.

553
00:42:08,881 --> 00:42:10,550
Do you not hear me?

554
00:42:10,633 --> 00:42:11,759
Yes, Your Royal Highness.

555
00:42:14,137 --> 00:42:15,346
Grand Prince…

556
00:42:18,808 --> 00:42:20,101
Your Majesty.

557
00:42:35,408 --> 00:42:37,577
Do you think I'm oblivious
to your scheming?

558
00:42:38,703 --> 00:42:39,704
[deeply exhales]

559
00:42:40,580 --> 00:42:42,874
[choking] Your… Royal…

560
00:42:44,417 --> 00:42:45,418
Your Royal Highness!

561
00:42:47,837 --> 00:42:48,838
Your Royal Highness.

562
00:42:49,422 --> 00:42:51,257
Please let him go first…

563
00:42:51,757 --> 00:42:53,926
Are you afraid I will become king?

564
00:42:59,390 --> 00:43:01,434
If you wish to drive me from the palace,

565
00:43:03,144 --> 00:43:04,353
you will

566
00:43:05,021 --> 00:43:06,522
have to kill me first.

567
00:43:08,191 --> 00:43:09,525
Your Royal Highness!

568
00:43:11,694 --> 00:43:13,321
[choking, coughing]

569
00:43:16,199 --> 00:43:18,159
If you threaten my nephew again…

570
00:43:20,870 --> 00:43:22,622
you shall not be granted a merciful death.

571
00:43:35,801 --> 00:43:37,803
[choking, panting continues]

572
00:43:48,898 --> 00:43:50,274
Uncle…

573
00:43:58,991 --> 00:44:00,952
THAT DAY, 3 YEARS AGO

574
00:44:03,955 --> 00:44:05,873
The Queen is inside.

575
00:44:05,957 --> 00:44:08,000
Please wait here for a moment.

576
00:44:09,126 --> 00:44:10,127
Understood.

577
00:44:13,172 --> 00:44:15,383
-[King] Uncle!
-[chuckles]

578
00:44:19,345 --> 00:44:20,346
[chuckles]

579
00:44:25,226 --> 00:44:27,228
[muttering]

580
00:44:35,569 --> 00:44:37,905
[Yun] You intend for Grand Prince I-AN
to ascend the throne?

581
00:44:39,824 --> 00:44:42,576
Have you truly gone mad?

582
00:44:48,624 --> 00:44:50,584
[royal] It will be better than dying.

583
00:44:52,503 --> 00:44:54,297
[Yun] It would be better to die.

584
00:45:05,141 --> 00:45:06,600
I would rather see you dead.

585
00:45:08,769 --> 00:45:10,479
For the sake of the Crown Prince.

586
00:45:12,523 --> 00:45:13,816
[royal] My Queen!

587
00:45:25,828 --> 00:45:26,829
Your Majesty.

588
00:45:26,912 --> 00:45:27,913
Yes…

589
00:45:33,252 --> 00:45:35,087
[crying]

590
00:45:47,641 --> 00:45:48,642
Your Majesty.

591
00:45:49,435 --> 00:45:50,436
[King] Yes?
STYLE
::cue()

592
00:45:54,732 --> 00:45:55,775
If you are ever scared…

593
00:45:56,359 --> 00:45:58,361
[♪ gentle music playing]

594
00:46:01,989 --> 00:46:03,199
…you must come to me.

595
00:46:06,869 --> 00:46:07,912
Whenever that may be.

596
00:46:29,308 --> 00:46:30,518
Come to me…

597
00:46:33,771 --> 00:46:34,772
whenever you get scared.

598
00:46:38,692 --> 00:46:41,112
Yes, Uncle.

599
00:47:14,061 --> 00:47:15,062
What's wrong?

600
00:47:15,646 --> 00:47:16,689
What?

601
00:47:17,731 --> 00:47:19,358
Did you wrong me somehow?

602
00:47:23,612 --> 00:47:24,655
Earlier…

603
00:47:28,576 --> 00:47:29,577
Sorry.

604
00:47:31,579 --> 00:47:32,580
For what?

605
00:47:33,706 --> 00:47:34,999
That unpleasant sight.

606
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,001
[chuckles]

607
00:47:37,626 --> 00:47:38,669
I thought it was pleasant.

608
00:47:40,129 --> 00:47:41,464
What?

609
00:47:41,547 --> 00:47:42,548
You did well.

610
00:47:44,467 --> 00:47:45,968
You must fight back

611
00:47:47,303 --> 00:47:48,304
if you wish…

612
00:47:50,556 --> 00:47:52,224
to protect something.

613
00:48:02,902 --> 00:48:04,904
[♪ tense music playing]

614
00:48:13,954 --> 00:48:15,247
[sighs]

615
00:48:15,331 --> 00:48:16,832
Any likes or dislikes?

616
00:48:18,083 --> 00:48:19,084
All of a sudden?

617
00:48:20,586 --> 00:48:23,589
Well, I like…

618
00:48:24,924 --> 00:48:28,511
Flowers. I do like them the most.

619
00:48:31,639 --> 00:48:32,848
What?

620
00:48:33,974 --> 00:48:36,060
-Not you.
-Pardon?

621
00:48:36,644 --> 00:48:38,270
What does the Grand Prince like?

622
00:48:39,146 --> 00:48:40,397
Oh. I see.

623
00:48:40,481 --> 00:48:41,941
The Grand Prince.

624
00:48:42,024 --> 00:48:43,734
-[chuckling] So silly.
-Unbelievable.

625
00:48:43,817 --> 00:48:46,028
Why do you ask?

626
00:48:46,570 --> 00:48:49,573
More stress is
the only thing waiting for him.

627
00:48:49,657 --> 00:48:51,867
I thought I could do
something nice for him.

628
00:48:51,951 --> 00:48:53,827
Maybe a favorite snack or music?

629
00:48:55,663 --> 00:48:56,956
Let me think.

630
00:48:57,581 --> 00:48:59,833
Black tea? He likes black tea.

631
00:49:00,793 --> 00:49:03,087
He also likes bitter chocolate.

632
00:49:05,130 --> 00:49:06,131
What about music?

633
00:49:06,215 --> 00:49:08,467
Nope. He doesn't like anything loud.

634
00:49:08,551 --> 00:49:09,718
Mmm.

635
00:49:10,678 --> 00:49:12,972
What about his favorite scent?

636
00:49:13,055 --> 00:49:14,306
Scent?

637
00:49:14,390 --> 00:49:15,975
Like incense sticks or diffusers.

638
00:49:16,058 --> 00:49:19,103
That will get you kicked out instantly.

639
00:49:19,186 --> 00:49:23,399
He flipped out the last time
I put on some cologne.

640
00:49:25,192 --> 00:49:26,819
Noted. I should stop.

641
00:49:30,406 --> 00:49:32,575
Did you show
the Grand Princess the same care?

642
00:49:33,576 --> 00:49:34,577
Yes.

643
00:49:35,077 --> 00:49:37,246
One works best without distractions.

644
00:49:43,377 --> 00:49:44,670
What about you, Hyejeong?

645
00:49:47,423 --> 00:49:48,424
Pardon?

646
00:49:49,925 --> 00:49:53,679
I mean, it looks like you just know
the names of flowers.

647
00:49:53,762 --> 00:49:55,848
You don't seem that crazy about tea.

648
00:49:58,142 --> 00:50:00,894
What do you like, Hyejeong?

649
00:50:03,230 --> 00:50:04,857
[♪ romantic pop music playing]

650
00:50:04,940 --> 00:50:06,066
Well…

651
00:50:12,615 --> 00:50:13,616
I…

652
00:50:18,495 --> 00:50:19,538
I was

653
00:50:20,664 --> 00:50:21,999
just curious. That's all.

654
00:50:24,710 --> 00:50:25,794
Such nice weather.
STYLE
::cue()

655
00:50:38,015 --> 00:50:40,017
[music continues]

656
00:50:43,937 --> 00:50:44,938
[I-AN grunts]

657
00:51:13,717 --> 00:51:14,760
[I-AN] I'm scared

658
00:51:16,345 --> 00:51:17,638
that my honor will end up…

659
00:51:21,558 --> 00:51:22,559
harming you.

660
00:51:26,897 --> 00:51:27,898
Me too.

661
00:51:31,652 --> 00:51:33,529
I'm scared I might end up…

662
00:51:36,532 --> 00:51:37,741
ruining you.

663
00:52:10,190 --> 00:52:13,569
Seong Huiju!
I know public opinion's in the gutter,

664
00:52:13,652 --> 00:52:15,571
but a prosecutor's investigation?
Seriously?

665
00:52:16,113 --> 00:52:17,740
I'm dying over here with tanking stocks.

666
00:52:17,823 --> 00:52:20,868
What the hell are you talking about?

667
00:52:28,083 --> 00:52:30,753
All the board members
have been subpoenaed.

668
00:52:33,464 --> 00:52:35,591
Father is about to be summoned
at this rate.

669
00:52:38,177 --> 00:52:40,471
Okay, I'll be there this afternoon.

670
00:52:42,765 --> 00:52:43,932
What's wrong?

671
00:52:44,016 --> 00:52:45,517
Is something happening at the company?

672
00:52:45,601 --> 00:52:48,520
No. I guess Father is a bit unwell.

673
00:52:48,604 --> 00:52:49,646
The chairman?

674
00:52:50,230 --> 00:52:52,024
-Then we should visit him--
-No need for all that.

675
00:52:52,608 --> 00:52:55,611
That will only end up attracting a crowd.

676
00:52:55,694 --> 00:52:57,321
It'll be better if I make
a quick run with Aide Choi.

677
00:52:57,404 --> 00:52:59,615
-It's nothing serious anyway.
-But still…

678
00:52:59,698 --> 00:53:01,492
You two need to attend court.

679
00:53:02,075 --> 00:53:03,160
Go on.

680
00:53:03,243 --> 00:53:06,079
Let's have another productive day today.

681
00:53:06,914 --> 00:53:07,915
I'll call you.

682
00:53:08,499 --> 00:53:09,625
Good luck!

683
00:53:17,841 --> 00:53:19,009
Get a car ready.

684
00:53:19,676 --> 00:53:21,386
You want to go now?

685
00:53:21,470 --> 00:53:22,888
Not an escort vehicle.

686
00:53:24,014 --> 00:53:25,432
One that I can drive.

687
00:53:26,099 --> 00:53:27,100
Understood.

688
00:53:37,945 --> 00:53:39,947
[♪ energetic music playing]

689
00:54:06,890 --> 00:54:08,141
What do I have to do?

690
00:54:10,769 --> 00:54:12,312
You must know.

691
00:54:13,355 --> 00:54:16,066
Both the company and the palace
are a complete train wreck.

692
00:54:16,149 --> 00:54:18,068
And there's nothing I can do.

693
00:54:18,151 --> 00:54:19,486
At this rate…

694
00:54:21,488 --> 00:54:22,781
[sighs]

695
00:54:25,701 --> 00:54:26,952
So tell me.

696
00:54:29,204 --> 00:54:30,539
Tell me what I should do.

697
00:54:35,711 --> 00:54:36,920
[sighs]

698
00:54:38,672 --> 00:54:39,673
For now,

699
00:54:41,133 --> 00:54:42,217
do nothing.

700
00:54:42,801 --> 00:54:45,887
-What?
-I'll make sure you don't get hurt, so--

701
00:54:45,971 --> 00:54:47,431
I'm not asking you to protect me.

702
00:54:53,520 --> 00:54:55,480
You're not even pretending now?

703
00:54:58,483 --> 00:54:59,484
What?

704
00:54:59,568 --> 00:55:00,902
You said it was all for show.

705
00:55:01,903 --> 00:55:02,904
You and the Grand Prince.

706
00:55:12,748 --> 00:55:13,999
I don't think that's true now.
STYLE
::cue()

707
00:55:15,292 --> 00:55:17,461
[♪ tender music playing]

708
00:55:17,544 --> 00:55:18,837
What's that supposed to mean?

709
00:55:25,135 --> 00:55:26,219
I like him.

710
00:55:27,554 --> 00:55:28,555
The Grand Prince.

711
00:55:33,185 --> 00:55:34,227
A lot.

712
00:55:47,240 --> 00:55:48,241
That is…

713
00:55:52,579 --> 00:55:53,580
quite unfortunate.

714
00:56:17,479 --> 00:56:19,147
To the chairman now?

715
00:56:26,947 --> 00:56:27,948
Let's go now.

716
00:56:28,949 --> 00:56:30,075
Yes, Your Royal Highness.

717
00:56:32,828 --> 00:56:34,162
I messed up.

718
00:56:39,710 --> 00:56:41,503
What are you doing?

719
00:56:41,586 --> 00:56:42,629
Huiju.

720
00:56:43,922 --> 00:56:45,590
I deceived you…

721
00:56:48,343 --> 00:56:49,970
and hurt the company.

722
00:56:53,181 --> 00:56:54,599
I'm sorry for all of it.

723
00:57:00,021 --> 00:57:01,022
Please help me.

724
00:57:15,996 --> 00:57:17,789
Just this once, please help me, Father.

725
00:57:20,959 --> 00:57:22,252
I want to make things right…

726
00:57:24,880 --> 00:57:26,339
but I don't know how.

727
00:57:33,388 --> 00:57:35,348
And you call yourself a businesswoman…

728
00:57:40,437 --> 00:57:41,646
[sniffles]

729
00:57:44,316 --> 00:57:45,317
Tell me.

730
00:57:46,359 --> 00:57:48,195
Who are you trying to save here? Yourself?

731
00:57:48,695 --> 00:57:49,905
Or the Grand Prince?

732
00:58:12,844 --> 00:58:15,472
Um, I heard you enjoyed black tea.

733
00:58:18,892 --> 00:58:19,893
Thank you.

734
00:58:26,566 --> 00:58:29,277
Perhaps you might consider
taking a few days off?

735
00:58:31,613 --> 00:58:34,032
[sighs] What's going on?

736
00:58:35,492 --> 00:58:40,121
The Prime Minister's Office has requested
that you cease your official duties.

737
00:58:42,457 --> 00:58:43,458
[scoffs]

738
00:58:44,084 --> 00:58:45,085
A request?

739
00:58:49,172 --> 00:58:50,882
-Maybe just for a few days…
-[phone buzzes]

740
00:58:51,883 --> 00:58:53,510
NEW MESSAGE

741
00:58:54,094 --> 00:58:55,345
[Huiju] I'll be there soon.

742
00:58:59,099 --> 00:59:01,810
Do not say anything to my wife.

743
00:59:02,519 --> 00:59:04,563
Yes, Your Royal Highness.
STYLE
::cue()

744
01:00:00,827 --> 01:00:01,828
Your Royal Highness.

745
01:00:08,418 --> 01:00:09,794
How's your father doing?

746
01:00:17,928 --> 01:00:19,638
What's this? A gift?

747
01:00:25,185 --> 01:00:26,186
Your Royal Highness.

748
01:00:28,313 --> 01:00:29,314
Yes?

749
01:00:40,867 --> 01:00:42,077
Let's get a divorce.

750
01:00:54,422 --> 01:00:56,424
[♪ romantic pop music playing]

751
01:01:18,279 --> 01:01:19,572
EPILOGUE

752
01:01:19,656 --> 01:01:20,657
Tell me.

753
01:01:21,199 --> 01:01:22,951
Who are you trying to save here? Yourself?

754
01:01:23,034 --> 01:01:24,452
Or the Grand Prince?

755
01:01:31,835 --> 01:01:32,919
Him.

756
01:01:37,632 --> 01:01:39,676
I can save myself.

757
01:01:43,221 --> 01:01:44,222
You…

758
01:01:47,767 --> 01:01:49,352
Please, Father.

759
01:01:59,195 --> 01:02:02,115
PERFECT CROWN

760
01:02:38,735 --> 01:02:40,236
I want to cut my losses.

761
01:02:40,820 --> 01:02:42,113
Let's get a divorce.

762
01:02:43,364 --> 01:02:44,699
[I-AN] Is this how it felt?

763
01:02:46,242 --> 01:02:48,328
[Hyejeong] Are they really
going to get divorced?

764
01:02:48,411 --> 01:02:51,206
[Jeongwoo] You must stop either
the Grand Prince or His Majesty.

765
01:02:51,289 --> 01:02:52,707
Do whatever you must.

766
01:02:52,791 --> 01:02:54,000
[Huiju] But you lost it all.

767
01:02:54,584 --> 01:02:56,294
What could you possibly do for me now?

768
01:02:56,878 --> 01:02:57,879
Did you truly believe

769
01:02:57,962 --> 01:03:00,757
I could not protect us?

770
01:03:00,840 --> 01:03:02,509
[Yun] Surely you do not intend to accept.

771
01:03:02,592 --> 01:03:05,887
I need the girl I hid
brought to the palace.

772
01:03:05,970 --> 01:03:07,514
[I-AN] You did not trust me.

773
01:03:09,599 --> 01:03:11,392
[Lady Choi] The palace gates
will be shut soon.

774
01:03:12,727 --> 01:03:13,770
[Huiju] Let's see this through.

775
01:03:14,854 --> 01:03:15,939
I will be by your side.

776
01:03:17,690 --> 01:03:19,692
Translated by Justin S. Kim

777
01:03:30,995 --> 01:03:34,707
PERFECT CROWN
